div.p:
Alpha, omega (?) Good fortune. In the reign of Tiberius Julius Doiptounos, pious king, friend of Caesar and of the Romans, this tower was erected; 
               and in the time of governor Eisgoudios and prefect (Comes) secretary Spadinos, the head of prefects (comites) Sauagos, and his superintendent of 
            the works [...], on the 20th of the month Gorgipiaios, in the charge of master builder [...]. [In the year 7... (?)].
